1
00:01:49,159 --> 00:01:50,200
So you're Xing Wu?

2
00:01:51,920 --> 00:01:53,120
I'm Ye's father.

3
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:55,560
Tomorrow I'm taking her away.

4
00:01:58,519 --> 00:01:59,159
I know.

5
00:02:01,079 --> 00:02:02,719
I came to you because I need

6
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:03,760
a favor.

7
00:02:04,959 --> 00:02:05,560
Go ahead.

8
00:02:06,640 --> 00:02:07,879
After Ye goes back to Beijing,

9
00:02:08,759 --> 00:02:09,520
I don't want you two

10
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:10,759
to have any contact.

11
00:02:15,199 --> 00:02:16,719
You shouldn't be asking me this.

12
00:02:17,560 --> 00:02:19,439
She's free to decide

13
00:02:20,439 --> 00:02:21,439
who she keeps in touch with.

14
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:27,240
She's my daughter.

15
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:30,159
As her father,

16
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:32,080
I won't let anyone

17
00:02:32,879 --> 00:02:34,759
get in the way of her bright future.

18
00:02:36,919 --> 00:02:37,800
Ye still has

19
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:39,199
unrealistic expectations about reality.

20
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:41,360
But once she's back in Beijing,

21
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:42,159
she'll realize

22
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:45,039
you're from different worlds.

23
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:47,919
As time goes by,

24
00:02:48,439 --> 00:02:49,599
she'll forget about you.

25
00:02:50,560 --> 00:02:51,400
You won't

26
00:02:52,039 --> 00:02:53,439
cross paths again in the future.

27
00:02:57,960 --> 00:02:58,919
It's fine if she forgets.

28
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:01,039
As long as she's doing well.

29
00:03:03,439 --> 00:03:04,520
If there's nothing else,

30
00:03:05,719 --> 00:03:06,400
I'll head off.

31
00:03:15,960 --> 00:03:16,520
Mr. Qing,

32
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:18,599
after Qing Ye goes back,

33
00:03:19,879 --> 00:03:21,319
please spend more time

34
00:03:21,319 --> 00:03:21,919
with her.

35
00:03:23,039 --> 00:03:23,919
She's strong

36
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:25,319
and independent,

37
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:28,280
but she also gets lonely.

38
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:31,960
She needs her family to love her.

39
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:05,960
Leaving so suddenly.

40
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:08,560
I didn't prepare anything.

41
00:04:10,199 --> 00:04:11,520
Don't even have anything decent

42
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:12,159
to give you.

43
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:17,399
Your hairdressing skills are decent.

44
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:20,360
Just give me a nice hairstyle.

45
00:04:21,199 --> 00:04:21,759
That'd be perfect.

46
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:24,000
You're so sweet.

47
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:27,439
I had hair as nice as yours

48
00:04:28,519 --> 00:04:31,160
when I was young.

49
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:35,800
You must've been beautiful back then.

50
00:04:37,439 --> 00:04:38,360
Not really.

51
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:40,120
But I was stupid.

52
00:04:42,240 --> 00:04:43,319
Back then,

53
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:44,720
I was dating a guy

54
00:04:44,839 --> 00:04:46,519
my mom didn't approve of.

55
00:04:46,959 --> 00:04:48,120
Your mom also told me

56
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:50,079
to break up with him.

57
00:04:50,839 --> 00:04:51,720
But I wouldn't listen.

58
00:04:52,199 --> 00:04:53,399
I thought they didn't know anything.

59
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:55,240
They didn't get me.

60
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:57,160
They didn't understand love.

61
00:04:57,879 --> 00:04:58,920
So I got mad

62
00:04:59,199 --> 00:05:00,759
and ran off with that guy.

63
00:05:02,240 --> 00:05:02,920
And

64
00:05:03,519 --> 00:05:04,040
I ended up

65
00:05:04,040 --> 00:05:05,560
like this.

66
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:11,439
I regret it so much.

67
00:05:13,399 --> 00:05:14,279
But life

68
00:05:15,399 --> 00:05:16,839
doesn't give you do-overs.

69
00:05:20,439 --> 00:05:21,839
Don't be mad at your dad.

70
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:24,920
Don't choose the wrong path

71
00:05:25,959 --> 00:05:27,040
just out of spite.

72
00:05:28,240 --> 00:05:29,160
No parent

73
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:30,759
in this world

74
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:32,399
would harm their own child.

75
00:05:40,439 --> 00:05:42,120
How do I know what the right choice is?

76
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:55,240
Come on.

77
00:05:56,759 --> 00:05:57,680
Let me see.

78
00:06:00,879 --> 00:06:01,360
Okay.

79
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:04,720
Go home with your dad.

80
00:06:06,519 --> 00:06:07,639
You'll have a big house

81
00:06:08,399 --> 00:06:10,000
and pretty clothes.

82
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:12,199
When you want to study,

83
00:06:12,639 --> 00:06:14,079
you can study.

84
00:06:14,519 --> 00:06:15,680
When you want to have fun,

85
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:17,160
you can have fun.

86
00:06:18,439 --> 00:06:20,720
You'll never have to worry about money.

87
00:06:21,399 --> 00:06:23,519
That's the right choice.

88
00:06:28,519 --> 00:06:29,120
Done.

89
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:34,079
Auntie.

90
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:38,360
This hairstyle looks really good.

91
00:06:41,199 --> 00:06:42,040
My skills

92
00:06:42,759 --> 00:06:43,560
are

93
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:45,120
pretty solid.

94
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:49,199
Ye, you look beautiful.

95
00:09:44,879 --> 00:09:45,480
You're awake.

96
00:09:55,279 --> 00:09:56,600
I woke up as soon as you came in.

97
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:00,440
I...

98
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:02,639
got you some candied hawthorn.

99
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:05,279
I'm leaving tomorrow.

100
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:15,440
I heard.

101
00:10:20,840 --> 00:10:21,639
This is the last night.

102
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:24,399
I wanted to do something.

103
00:10:25,639 --> 00:10:26,480
It feels like

104
00:10:27,759 --> 00:10:28,919
a waste

105
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:31,600
to just sleep through it.

106
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:39,960
What do you wanna do?

107
00:10:41,320 --> 00:10:41,960
I'm with you.

108
00:10:57,840 --> 00:10:59,120
This is the first time

109
00:10:59,919 --> 00:11:00,879
in so long

110
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:03,039
I've just

111
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:05,120
quietly watched

112
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:07,279
the sea in Zhazhating.

113
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:10,200
Like an oil painting.

114
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:13,240
It looks more like

115
00:11:14,159 --> 00:11:15,200
a circuit board.

116
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:18,320
How?

117
00:11:18,879 --> 00:11:19,840
You're killing the mood.

118
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:23,919
Look over there.

119
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:26,240
I used to

120
00:11:27,159 --> 00:11:28,399
climb up there all the time as a kid.

121
00:11:30,279 --> 00:11:32,480
Your secret base?

122
00:11:34,159 --> 00:11:34,720
Kind of.

123
00:11:35,360 --> 00:11:36,879
Back then, Xing Guodong had a bad temper

124
00:11:37,360 --> 00:11:38,000
and always hit people.

125
00:11:38,799 --> 00:11:39,720
So I'd

126
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:40,799
sneak far away by myself

127
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:42,720
and climb up there.

128
00:11:43,399 --> 00:11:44,519
He wouldn't find you?

129
00:11:45,240 --> 00:11:45,679
No.

130
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:47,159
Never.

131
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:49,279
I used to sit up there

132
00:11:49,279 --> 00:11:50,080
for the whole day.

133
00:11:50,879 --> 00:11:51,840
Until the sun

134
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:53,559
slowly set,

135
00:11:54,120 --> 00:11:55,000
the fishing boats came back,

136
00:11:55,519 --> 00:11:56,679
and the sky got dark.

137
00:11:59,879 --> 00:12:00,559
Weren't you scared?

138
00:12:00,919 --> 00:12:01,480
I was.

139
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:03,200
I was terrified as a kid.

140
00:12:03,639 --> 00:12:04,639
I didn't feel it while climbing up.

141
00:12:05,279 --> 00:12:06,320
But it was windy out there.

142
00:12:07,159 --> 00:12:08,279
And then I was too scared to climb down.

143
00:12:08,639 --> 00:12:09,080
So...

144
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:11,120
So what did you do? Then what?

145
00:12:11,279 --> 00:12:12,039
So I'd wait.

146
00:12:12,759 --> 00:12:13,519
Wait until it got dark.

147
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:15,480
Wait until the lighthouse lit up.

148
00:12:15,840 --> 00:12:17,840
I thought that light was shining for me.

149
00:12:18,720 --> 00:12:19,879
And suddenly, I wasn't scared anymore.

150
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:26,000
After that, I'd often

151
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:27,000
climb up there alone

152
00:12:27,919 --> 00:12:29,399
and wait for the lighthouse to light up.

153
00:12:33,559 --> 00:12:34,440
Just like now.

154
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:36,639
Five.

155
00:12:37,279 --> 00:12:37,840
Four.

156
00:12:38,320 --> 00:12:38,840
Three.
Two.

157
00:12:40,840 --> 00:12:41,320
One.
Light.

158
00:12:52,399 --> 00:12:53,080
It's late.

159
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:54,360
Light!

160
00:13:03,440 --> 00:13:04,799
Do you know what a lighthouse is for?

161
00:13:06,559 --> 00:13:07,120
Coordinates?

162
00:13:07,840 --> 00:13:08,399
Exactly.

163
00:13:09,080 --> 00:13:10,600
A lighthouse is an important

164
00:13:10,679 --> 00:13:12,600
navigation beacon to guide ships.

165
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:20,519
Qing Ye.

166
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:23,639
You're a born explorer.

167
00:13:25,120 --> 00:13:26,159
Time to set sail.

168
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:29,120
Go conquer your vast ocean.

169
00:13:36,840 --> 00:13:38,519
Zhazhating really has some kind of

170
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:40,639
invisible pull.

171
00:13:43,639 --> 00:13:45,039
First time I came,

172
00:13:46,159 --> 00:13:47,240
I really wanted to leave.

173
00:13:48,519 --> 00:13:49,879
Second time I came,

174
00:13:50,559 --> 00:13:51,639
I really wanted to stay.

175
00:13:52,639 --> 00:13:53,559
This time,

176
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:57,360
I think

177
00:14:01,360 --> 00:14:02,000
it'd be great

178
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:03,320
if you could come with me.

179
00:14:12,840 --> 00:14:13,840
After you leave this time,

180
00:14:15,879 --> 00:14:16,840
don't come back.

181
00:14:20,759 --> 00:14:21,720
Do you remember

182
00:14:24,720 --> 00:14:25,600
what you said to me

183
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:26,759
that night during New Year's?

184
00:14:33,039 --> 00:14:33,759
I do.

185
00:14:34,919 --> 00:14:36,200
You said wherever I want to go,

186
00:14:37,639 --> 00:14:38,480
you'll be there.

187
00:14:44,360 --> 00:14:45,720
But with my grades right now,

188
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:49,360
I can't

189
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:51,039
get into the same university as you,

190
00:14:51,039 --> 00:14:52,080
let alone go abroad.

191
00:14:53,039 --> 00:14:53,879
That's just the truth.

192
00:15:07,519 --> 00:15:08,200
Xing Wu,

193
00:15:09,240 --> 00:15:10,039
I believe in you.

194
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:12,279
If you really want to go,

195
00:15:13,559 --> 00:15:15,440
there are a million ways to get there.

196
00:15:17,799 --> 00:15:19,320
If you want to see me again,

197
00:15:21,320 --> 00:15:23,200
then walk right up to me yourself.

198
00:15:31,759 --> 00:15:32,320
Okay.

199
00:15:34,240 --> 00:15:35,000
I promise you.

200
00:15:46,519 --> 00:15:49,159
I'll apply to Qingbei University.

201
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:51,759
I'll cut the distance between us

202
00:15:52,840 --> 00:15:53,759
in half.

203
00:15:55,279 --> 00:15:56,120
The rest

204
00:15:59,120 --> 00:16:00,159
is up to you.

205
00:16:08,159 --> 00:16:08,840
I'll do my best.

206
00:16:12,360 --> 00:16:13,200
Give me your phone.

207
00:16:35,919 --> 00:16:36,600
I'll delete

208
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:37,799
our contact.

209
00:16:40,399 --> 00:16:41,759
We won't be in touch again

210
00:16:44,840 --> 00:16:46,000
until you catch up to me.

211
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:27,839
Think of this as motivation.

212
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:30,680
So you can keep up with me.

213
00:17:38,440 --> 00:17:39,759
I hope the next time

214
00:17:39,759 --> 00:17:40,640
we see each other,

215
00:17:42,039 --> 00:17:43,640
we'll both be at our best.

216
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:06,880
Qing Ye.

217
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:11,079
Just keep moving forward.

218
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:14,880
I'll catch up.

219
00:19:12,559 --> 00:19:13,640
You should head back now.

220
00:19:13,960 --> 00:19:15,119
You've got work tomorrow.

221
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:20,200
I'll watch you go in,

222
00:19:21,319 --> 00:19:21,960
then I'll leave.

223
00:19:37,079 --> 00:19:38,160
Will you come tomorrow?

224
00:19:50,759 --> 00:19:51,359
Qing Ye.

225
00:19:53,599 --> 00:19:54,400
Don't look back.

226
00:22:23,519 --> 00:22:24,599
Forget it.

227
00:22:24,599 --> 00:22:26,119
You're not helping.

228
00:22:27,400 --> 00:22:28,400
After rushing so much,

229
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:29,920
this is all I managed to knit.

230
00:22:30,559 --> 00:22:32,279
Qing Ye is leaving first thing tomorrow.

231
00:22:32,480 --> 00:22:33,680
How am I gonna finish in time?

232
00:22:34,920 --> 00:22:36,839
Qing Ye's dad really is something.

233
00:22:37,759 --> 00:22:38,839
Coming so suddenly.

234
00:22:39,519 --> 00:22:40,920
Leaving so suddenly too.

235
00:22:41,559 --> 00:22:42,960
We didn't have any time to prepare.

236
00:22:44,920 --> 00:22:45,680
You know,

237
00:22:45,680 --> 00:22:47,079
Ye never gets to enjoy any comfort

238
00:22:47,240 --> 00:22:48,720
while she's here with us.

239
00:22:49,599 --> 00:22:51,480
Going back with her dad is for the best.

240
00:23:46,119 --> 00:23:46,759
Get in.

241
00:23:49,680 --> 00:23:50,359
Where's your luggage?

242
00:23:51,759 --> 00:23:52,720
It's still early.

243
00:23:53,920 --> 00:23:54,480
Dad.

244
00:23:55,680 --> 00:23:56,920
Let me take you to breakfast.

245
00:24:18,839 --> 00:24:19,559
Here.

246
00:24:20,119 --> 00:24:20,920
Try our signature

247
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:22,640
seafood noodles.

248
00:24:22,720 --> 00:24:23,319
Thanks.

249
00:24:24,519 --> 00:24:25,240
Thanks.

250
00:24:26,359 --> 00:24:27,480
Let me know if you want anything.

251
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:28,759
Ye, take your time eating.

252
00:24:28,839 --> 00:24:30,000
Thanks, Auntie Shanxi.

253
00:24:34,720 --> 00:24:35,480
So

254
00:24:36,359 --> 00:24:37,440
the family you're staying with

255
00:24:37,440 --> 00:24:38,359
runs a restaurant.

256
00:24:38,920 --> 00:24:39,400
Yes.

257
00:24:40,440 --> 00:24:43,400
They gave us their house to live in.

258
00:24:43,839 --> 00:24:45,359
They're staying somewhere else for now.

259
00:24:47,799 --> 00:24:49,440
No need to wipe it. It's clean.

260
00:24:49,640 --> 00:24:50,680
Been through the sterilizer.

261
00:24:55,319 --> 00:24:56,880
You used to be such a germaphobe.

262
00:24:59,839 --> 00:25:00,839
This place cures germaphobia.

263
00:25:01,480 --> 00:25:03,000
Stay long enough and you'll get used to it.

264
00:25:10,400 --> 00:25:10,920
See that place

265
00:25:10,920 --> 00:25:12,039
across the way that had a fire?

266
00:25:14,039 --> 00:25:14,799
I used to

267
00:25:15,759 --> 00:25:16,759
live there.

268
00:25:20,759 --> 00:25:22,000
I came here years ago.

269
00:25:23,279 --> 00:25:24,720
Had no idea it turned out like this.

270
00:25:25,880 --> 00:25:26,759
At least you're okay.

271
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:29,079
When I first came here,

272
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:32,799
Auntie Lanfang's family cooked with lard.

273
00:25:33,599 --> 00:25:34,319
I couldn't get used to it.

274
00:25:35,799 --> 00:25:36,920
I went hungry for a day.

275
00:25:37,160 --> 00:25:38,400
The first proper meal I had

276
00:25:39,079 --> 00:25:40,359
was at this place.

277
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:47,240
I've let you down.

278
00:25:48,400 --> 00:25:49,240
You've been through a lot.

279
00:25:50,920 --> 00:25:52,200
Back then, I thought it was really hard.

280
00:25:54,480 --> 00:25:55,440
But looking back now,

281
00:25:56,599 --> 00:25:57,519
I was pretty happy.

282
00:26:02,519 --> 00:26:03,559
Ye, you've grown up.

283
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:06,119
You're not that little girl

284
00:26:06,119 --> 00:26:07,119
in my eyes anymore.

285
00:26:08,279 --> 00:26:09,880
Living in an environment like this,

286
00:26:10,799 --> 00:26:11,880
you have to learn

287
00:26:12,440 --> 00:26:13,400
to adjust

288
00:26:13,680 --> 00:26:14,480
and find joy in the hardship

289
00:26:14,920 --> 00:26:16,079
to get through the days.

290
00:26:16,920 --> 00:26:18,000
After coming here,

291
00:26:19,519 --> 00:26:20,359
I realized

292
00:26:22,200 --> 00:26:23,480
just how lonely it was

293
00:26:24,799 --> 00:26:26,359
back in Beijing after Mom passed away.

294
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:39,240
Dad,

295
00:26:41,079 --> 00:26:41,960
would you worry about

296
00:26:41,960 --> 00:26:43,039
whether others have enough to eat

297
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:45,440
when you're the one
going hungry?

298
00:26:49,359 --> 00:26:49,960
No.

299
00:26:54,640 --> 00:26:55,359
They would.

300
00:27:00,880 --> 00:27:01,440
The day Xing Wu found out

301
00:27:01,440 --> 00:27:02,599
I didn't like lard,

302
00:27:04,759 --> 00:27:06,200
he switched to rapeseed oil.

303
00:27:08,240 --> 00:27:08,960
Also

304
00:27:10,599 --> 00:27:12,000
the bathroom door lock in the backyard,

305
00:27:13,160 --> 00:27:13,799
the wardrobe,

306
00:27:14,720 --> 00:27:16,319
the air conditioner and lights in my room.

307
00:27:16,759 --> 00:27:17,440
Auntie Lanfang was worried

308
00:27:17,440 --> 00:27:18,480
I wasn't getting enough nutrition,

309
00:27:19,880 --> 00:27:20,720
so she kept making
braised pork trotters for me.

310
00:27:23,559 --> 00:27:24,960
Grandma was afraid I'd lose things again,

311
00:27:26,160 --> 00:27:27,039
so she knitted me all kinds of

312
00:27:27,039 --> 00:27:28,119
custom pen cases,

313
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:29,599
notebook covers,

314
00:27:30,319 --> 00:27:31,039
and laptop sleeves.

315
00:27:32,880 --> 00:27:34,000
These things might be

316
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:35,039
